// WebSocket Client
// Provides a WebSocket client with automatic reconnection, message subscription, and lifecycle events.
// Certain message types are also bridged to window CustomEvents for React hook consumption.

The singleton shared client is initialized lazily on first call to getWebSocketClient.
Reconnection uses exponential backoff: delays of 1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s (max 5 attempts).
Messages sent while disconnected are queued and flushed on reconnect.

Broadcast message types that are also dispatched as window CustomEvents:
  'status_changed', 'session_state_updated', 'task_graph_updated'

FUNCTION dispatchWebSocketEvent(type, detail)                           EXPORT
  Dispatch a window CustomEvent with the given type and detail payload.
  Used to decouple React hooks from direct WebSocket access.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.constructor(url)
  Store the URL. Initialize empty handler sets and state flags.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.connect() -> Promise<void>
  CALLS: flushPendingMessages (websocket), dispatchWebSocketEvent (websocket), onConnectionClosed (websocket)
  Open a new WebSocket to the stored URL.
  On open: reset reconnect counter, flush queued messages, notify connect handlers, resolve the promise.
  On message: parse JSON, bridge broadcast types to CustomEvents, then forward to all message handlers.
  On close: call onConnectionClosed.
  On error: log the error.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.disconnect()
  CALLS: onConnectionClosed (websocket)
  Mark as intentionally closed (prevents reconnection).
  Cancel any pending reconnect timer.
  Close and nullify the socket.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.send(message)
  If not connected, queue the message for later delivery.
  ELSE serialize to JSON and send. On send failure, re-queue the message.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.onMessage(handler) -> Subscription
  Register a message handler. Return an object with an unsubscribe method.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.onConnect(handler) -> Subscription
  Register a connect lifecycle handler. Return an object with an unsubscribe method.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.onDisconnect(handler) -> Subscription
  Register a disconnect lifecycle handler. Return an object with an unsubscribe method.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.isConnected() -> boolean
  Return true if the socket exists and is in the OPEN state.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.subscribe(channel)
  Send a { type: 'subscribe', channel } message.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.unsubscribe(channel)
  Send a { type: 'unsubscribe', channel } message.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.onConnectionClosed() [private]
  CALLS: scheduleReconnect (websocket)
  Nullify the socket. Notify all disconnect handlers.
  IF not intentionally closed and under max attempts, schedule a reconnect.

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.scheduleReconnect() [private]
  CALLS: connect (websocket)
  Calculate delay as reconnectDelay * 2^reconnectAttempts.
  Increment attempt counter. After the delay, call connect().

---

FUNCTION WebSocketClient.flushPendingMessages() [private]
  CALLS: send (websocket)
  Drain the pending message queue by calling send() on each queued message.

---

FUNCTION getWebSocketClient(url) -> WebSocketClient                     EXPORT
  CALLS: WebSocketClient (websocket), getDefaultWebSocketURL (websocket)
  IF the shared client doesn't exist, create one with the given URL (defaulting to getDefaultWebSocketURL).
  Return the shared client.

---

FUNCTION getDefaultWebSocketURL() -> string
  Return ws://<host>/ws (or wss:// if on HTTPS). In non-browser contexts, return ws://localhost:3737/ws.

---

FUNCTION resetWebSocketClient()                                         EXPORT
  Disconnect the shared client and set it to null. Used for testing.
